note: This flare is a long-duration event associated with a brightening visible in SDO AIA 131 from AR 12887 (near S28W59) around 2021-11-01T21:30Z.

The signature of this long-duration M-class flare can be seen in SDO AIA 131 toward the center of the Earth-facing disk around 2021-11-02T03:01Z. The end time is an estimate due to a second flare from AR 12887 occurring simultaneously.
The source signature of this flare is visible in SDO/AIA 131 and is associated with Active Region 12887.
The flare longitude might be slightly above 90 degrees as the Active Region 2887 had already rotated off the solar disk.
The signature of this flare is visible off the NW limb of the Earth-facing disk as seen in SDO AIA 131 after 2021-11-09T16:00Z.
